# Drizzle migrations

After changing `app/db/schema.ts`:

1. Run `npm run db:generate` — never hand-write `drizzle/*.sql` without a journal entry.
2. Commit the generated SQL, `drizzle/meta/_journal.json`, and snapshot together.
3. Run `npm run db:migrate` (or tell the user to).

`npm run db:migrate` only runs migrations registered in `drizzle/meta/_journal.json`. An orphan `drizzle/0027_foo.sql` file is ignored and causes runtime "column does not exist" errors.

Before finishing schema work, run `npm run db:check` (also runs in `typecheck`).

See `docs/database-migrations.md`.
